All 26 tests pass, but the acceptance criteria requires explicit coverage of **solvability**, **center reachability**, and **correct piece count** — all missing. I'll add these to `hedgePlacement.test.ts` (which has direct grid access) since they need BFS traversal on the maze grid.

`★ Insight ─────────────────────────────────────`
- A recursive backtracker produces a *perfect maze* (spanning tree) — every cell is reachable from every other. A BFS solvability test validates this property at the algorithm level.
- For "center is reachable", a BFS from the entrance cell to `[centerX][centerZ]` is the most meaningful test — it mirrors what the player must navigate.
- Piece count for a 12×12 maze: 144 cells, 143 spanning-tree passages removed from 264 internal walls + 48 boundary walls = ~169 walls remaining. Center clearing removes 4 more, so ~165. Asserting a range [120, 200] is a meaningful sanity check.
