`★ Insight ─────────────────────────────────────`
- The existing 26 tests in `mazeGenerator.test.ts` covered world-space structure well but lacked algorithmic guarantees. BFS solvability at the `hedgePlacement.ts` layer is the right level — it tests the maze *algorithm*, not the world-space wrapper.
- Recursive backtracker is a spanning-tree algorithm by construction: N cells → N-1 removed walls → one connected component. The BFS test directly validates this invariant (rather than trusting the algorithm theory).
